The paper deals with the application of compressed sensing to encryption, which falls under the information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR) sub-categories. The use of compressed sensing for signal processing and image compression is also discussed, which relates to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. The statistical analysis of the measurements and the investigation of performance bounds involve machine learning and statistical inference, which are relevant to the machine learning (cs.LG) and statistics (cs.SI) sub-categories.
